  "text": "The observation of two stages during devolatilization of plastics derived from electrical and electronic equipment is in agreement with the findings of other researchers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Vasile et al. [CITATION_3] studied devolatilization of keyboards and computer case, and reported that devolatilization starts at about 250°C, with release of halogenated compounds mainly due to presence of PVC. At temperatures higher than 370°C, releases of phenol and alkyl aromatic compounds were observed. Similar observation was reported for devolatilization of printed circuit board.",
